[2026-03-19T08:58:19.621Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018vK6RkYj4eqCzK9y1nXoPB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's what was done:\n\n**`config.ts`** — Added `metricsRetentionDays: number` to `OrchestratorConfig`, defaulting to `365` via `METRICS_RETENTION_DAYS` env var.\n\n**`db.ts`** — Added two new tables to the schema:\n- `daily_metrics` — per-persona, per-project daily aggregates (executions, tokens, cost, duration) with a unique constraint on `(project_id, persona_id, date)`\n- `system_daily_metrics` — system-wide daily aggregates (executions, tokens, cost, active personas/projects)\n\n**`retention.ts`** (new) — The retention engine:\n- `RetentionPolicy` interface — defines table, timestamp column, and lifecycle (`ephemeral`/`persistent`)\n- `TABLE_REGISTRY` — registers both metrics tables as ephemeral with `timestampColumn: 'date'`\n- `runRetention()` — deletes rows older than the configured retention window from all ephemeral tables\n- `startRetentionScheduler()` — runs retention immediately on startup, then hourly\n\n**`index.ts`** — Wired `startRetentionScheduler` into the main startup loop, passing `config.metricsRetentionDays`. Added cleanup on graceful shutdown."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":303,"cache_read_input_tokens":57496,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":303},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8c72731-09c7-48ee-b1d6-3b6918a239e2","uuid":"9d73258e-b8ca-4f43-80e6-df7c856cc492"}
